F16 Fighting Falcon


The General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon is a single-engine multirole fighter aircraft originally developed by General Dynamics for the United States Air Force. Designed as an air superiority day fighter, it evolved into a successful all-weather multirole aircraft.


First Flight: 1974

Engine Type :Single Engine

Range :4220 KM

Weight :9207 Kg
